<title>
Precaution for OBD System
</title>
<ptxt>
There are two types of OBD system, Euro-OBD system and non-Euro-OBD system, depending on the vehicle specification.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
As the diagnosis function is different between these two types, be sure to fully understand the OBD system. (OBD System Description)
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The simplest way to distinguish between Euro-OBD model and non-Euro-OBD model is to check whether the transmission warning light on the combination meter comes on or not when ignition is “ON”.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
